The paper discusses the use of mobile edge computing (MEC) for delivering virtual reality (VR) over wireless networks, which involves communication, caching, and computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves multimedia (VR) and optimization (resource allocation), which suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IT (Information Theory) as likely categories. The use of MEC also involves distributed computing, which suggests cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as a possible category. Finally, the paper involves decision-making and tradeoffs, which suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible category.
